Class ComplexContent

All Implemented Interfaces:
Content
public class ComplexContent
extends java.lang.Object
implements Content

Defines a content model for a complex type. A complexContent content model is used to create a complex type extends (adds new elements and/or attributes) OR restrict (removes elements from) an existing Type.

The default base type for a ComplexContent is a "ur-type".

addContent

public void addContent(Component component)
                throws SchemaException
Sets a component as a content of the complexContent. This method is called iteratively to set multiple components in the complex content. Valid components in a complexContent are AttributeGroupDefinition, Attribute, ModelGroup and ModelGroupDefinition
